The paper focuses on neural network architectures for high-resolution applications such as object detection and semantic segmentation, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the importance of efficiency in terms of memory traffic, which is a key concern in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper proposes a new network architecture, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
